{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Vue 3 + FastAPI\n      Composition API + Pinia stores. Rich component ecosystem including data grids, tabs, and form controls that mirror the existing ipywidgets UI closely.\n      \n        Browser (Vue 3 + Pinia)\n        Pinia stores ↔ Dexie.js (IndexedDB)\n        ECharts (vue-echarts) charts\n        ZIP export/import\n        Python (FastAPI)\n        Same stateless API surface as A\n      \n      \n        Pros\n          Largest component library ecosystem\n          PrimeVue / Naive UI for data grids/tables\n          Strong corporate backing (Evan You)\n          Gradual learning curve\n        \n        Cons\n          Heavier runtime than Svelte\n          More boilerplate for reactive data flows","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776851487849}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      SvelteKit + FastAPI ★ Recommended\n      Clean reactive stores map directly to the notebook widget pattern. Lightest runtime, best suited for data-heavy reactive UIs.\n      \n        Browser (SvelteKit)\n        Svelte stores ↔ Dexie.js (IndexedDB)\n        Plotly.js / ECharts charts\n        ZIP export/import\n        Python (FastAPI)\n        POST /preprocess → returns events+metrics JSON\n        POST /validate-schema → schema lint\n        bodaqs_analysis unchanged as library\n      \n      \n        Pros\n          Smallest runtime bundle (~5kb base)\n          Reactive stores ≈ existing widget contracts\n          First-class TypeScript + great tooling\n          SvelteKit routing suits multi-page app\n        \n        Cons\n          Smaller ecosystem than Vue/React\n          Less off-the-shelf UI component libraries","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1776851489074}
